"O problema con esta operativa reside, primeiramente, en que o Bug Tracker √© "
"un lugar demasiado pesado e torpe para manter unha discusi√≥n, e en segundo "
"termo en que outra xente probablemente non estea prestando atenci√≥n&mdash;"
"despois de todo, esperan que as discusi√≥ns de desenvolvemento se leven a "
"cabo na rolda de correo de desenvolvemento, polo que ese √© o lugar ao que "
"est√°n mirando. Probablemente non estean subscritos √° rolda de "
"notificaci√≥ns, e incluso se o est√°n, pode que non a sigan con demasiada "
"atenci√≥n."

#. Tag: para
#: ch06.xml:1607
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"But exactly where in the process did something go wrong? Was it when the "
"original person attached her solution to the issue&mdash;should she have "
"posted it to the list instead? Or was it when the second person responded in "
"the issue, instead of on the list?"
msgstr ""
"Pero, exactamente en que punto do proceso se fixo algo incorrecto? Foi no "
"momento no que a persoa orixinal engadiu a s√∫a soluci√≥n ao erro&mdash; "
"ter√≠a que telo enviado √° lista en lugar de engadilo? Ou foi cando a "
"segunda persoa respondeu √° incidencia, en lugar de facelo na rolda de "
"correo?"

#. Tag: para
#: ch06.xml:1613
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There isn't one right answer, but there is a general principle: if you're "
"just adding data to an issue, then do it in the tracker, but if you're "
"starting a <emphasis>conversation</emphasis>, then do it on the mailing "
"list. You may not always be able to tell which is the case, but just use "
"your best judgement. For example, when attaching a patch that contains a "
"potentially controversial solution, you might be able to anticipate that "
"people are going to have questions about it. So even though you would "
"normally attach the patch to the issue (assuming you don't want to or can't "
"commit the change directly), in this case you might choose to post it to a "
"mailing list instead. At any rate, there eventually will come a point in the "
"exchange where one party or the other can tell that it is about to go from "
"mere appending of data to an actual conversation&mdash;in the example that "
"started this section, that would be the second respondent, who on realizing "
"that there were problems with the patch, could predict that a real "
"conversation is about to ensue, and therefore that it should be held in the "
"appropriate medium."
msgstr ""
"Non hai unha resposta correcta, pero si que hai un principio xeral: se "
"simplemente est√°n engadindo datos a unha incidencia, ent√≥n faino no Bug "
"Tracker, pero se est√°s comezando unha <emphasis>conversa</emphasis>, ent√≥n "
"faino na rolda de correo. Non sempre poder√°s identificar cada caso, "
"simplemente emprega o teu xu√≠zo o mellor que poidas. Por exemplo, cando "
"achegues un parche que conte√±a unha soluci√≥n potencialmente controvertida, "
"debes anticipar que posiblemente haxa xente que te√±a preguntas sobre a "
"mesma. As√≠ que a√≠nda que normalmente achegues o parche conxuntamente coa "
"notificaci√≥n, (asumindo que non queres, ou non podes, facer o cambio "
"directamente), neste caso deber√≠as escoller enviar a mensaxe √° rolda de "
"correo en lugar de empregar o Bug Tracker. De todos xeitos, pode haber casos "
"nos que sexa dif√≠cil  En todo caso, eventualmente acontecer√° un momento "
"onde unha parte ou a outra indiquen que simplemente est√°n engadindo datos "
"√° conversaci√≥n actual&mdash;no exemplo que iniciaba esta secci√≥n, este "
"ser√≠a o segundo actor, o cal responde, quen d√°ndose conta de que hab√≠a "
"problemas co parche, puido predicir que √≠a a inciarse unha conversa sobre "
"el, e de a√≠ que debera facerse na canle apropiada."

#. Tag: para
#: ch06.xml:1631
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To use a mathematical analogy, if the information looks like it will be "
"quickly convergent, then put it directly in the bug tracker; if it looks "
"like it will be divergent, then a mailing list or IRC channel would be a "
"better place."
msgstr ""
"Empregando unha analox√≠a matem√°tica, se a informaci√≥n parece como que "
"vaia a ser rapidamente converxente, ent√≥n pona directamente no Bug Tracker; "
"se parece como se vaia haber diverxencias, ent√≥n unha rolda de correo ou "
"unha canle IRC ser√≠an un lugar mellor."

#. Tag: para
#: ch06.xml:1636
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This doesn't mean there should never be any exchanges in the bug tracker. "
"Asking for more details of the reproduction recipe from the original "
"reporter tends to be a highly convergent process, for instance. The person's "
"response is unlikely to raise new issues; it's simply going to flesh out "
"information already filed. There's no need to distract the mailing list with "
"that process; by all means, take care of it with a series of comments in the "
"tracker. Likewise, if you're fairly sure that the bug has been misreported "
